definitions.definition: ( physical chemistry ) Any of a set of stereoisomers characterized by a conformation that corresponds to a distinct potential energy minimum .
( physical chemistry , biochemistry ) A particular folded state or conformation of a protein , especially an abnormal conformation of a prion
